    <li class="comment even depth-2" id="li-comment-1288939">
        <article id="comment-1288939" class="comment">
            <div class="comment-content">

                                <p>Think, it you bought $35,000 of bitcoins in 2012, today it would be worth $1,400,000 CAD! Also, bitcoins are not fiat. Fiat means by decree, as in the government decrees what is to be used as money. Bitcoin&#8217;s value, like gold&#8217;s, was and is being determined in the free market. Also, although at first glance bitcoin appears to be created out of thin air, in reality it requires effort and cannot be created at will and without limit like fiat currencies. In this respect, again it is more akin to gold than fiat. Bitcoins are digital gold.</p>
                    <div style="clear:both;"></div>
